The paper discusses nonparallel support vector machines, which are commonly used in machine learning and pattern recognition. The paper focuses on comparing two types of frameworks for constructing nonparallel hyperplanes and proposes a new method for multiclass classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
